==English==
===Etymology===
OE. on char ajar, on the turn; AS. cerr, cyrr, turn, akin to G. kehren to turn, and to D. akerre.  See  [[Char]].

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ʌˈʤɑɹ/

===Adverb or Adjective===
# Slightly turned or opened; as, the door was standing ajar (adverb usage); the door is ajar (adjective usage).  The latter seems to be more common as of 2004.

